comment.body:
@Ansho Rei:

> The biggest problem is that it would not have file storage, so the plugin would always be leech-only.

Are you sure? I think that there are some browser APIs for storage in extensions.

@Ansho Rei:

>  but a lot of it won't be useful without the rest I imagine

It isn't just this. Some things (for the future) may also be that you could be able to use "core" ZeroNet protocol implementation easily for your custom application and without any additional frontend implementation (so that you would basically make your own custom frontend). Similar to how IPFS and some other protocols provide more "low-level" access which can be used to build custom applications easily.
